# Task 1 – Entity Relationship Diagram

## Project
Credit Card Approval Prediction Using Machine Learning

## Objective

Design an Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) representing the database structure of the Credit Card Approval Prediction System.

## Entities

- Users
- Applicant_Details
- Credit_History
- ML_Model
- Approval_Prediction

## Relationships

- One User → Many Applicants
- One Applicant → Many Credit History Records
- One Applicant → One Approval Prediction
- One ML Model → Many Predictions

## Technologies Used

- Draw.io / Lucidchart / Microsoft Visio
- Database Design Concepts

## Output

The ER Diagram represents the complete database schema for storing applicant information, historical credit records, machine learning model details, and approval predictions.

## Conclusion

The ER Diagram provides a structured foundation for implementing the database required by the Credit Card Approval Prediction System and ensures efficient data organization and integrity.
